# Bring-your-own-libsignal (Model B): Krypton does NOT embed Signal's binary.
# This cinterop compiles bindings from the headers only; the actual
# libsignal_ffi.a is supplied at LINK time by the consumer, who fetches it from
# Signal's official source on their own machine (scripts/fetch-libsignal-ffi.sh
# or build-libsignal-ffi.sh) and points the linker at it with -L<dir>.
#
# `linkerOpts = -lsignal_ffi` is recorded in the published klib so the consumer
# only needs to add the -L search path. No Signal binary is shipped by Krypton —
# the trust anchor is Signal, and there is nothing of ours to suspect.
headers = krypton_ffi.h
headerFilter = krypton_ffi.*
linkerOpts = -lsignal_ffi
